Czech market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  AAA Auto Group NV (AAA)   gained the most in almost four
weeks, rising 3.2 percent to 18.6 koruna. The Czech used-car
dealer may report a record profit for 2011 of more than 7
million euros ($9.3 million), Lidove Noviny newspaper reported
today, citing Chief Executive Officer Anthony Denny.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)   of Austria jumped 2 percent
to 475 koruna.  Komercni Banka AS (KOMB)  , the Czech unit of
Societe Generale SA, rose 2.9 percent to 3,710 koruna.  Global stocks rallied, with financial companies among the
biggest gainers after Greek lawmakers approved a fiscal-
